Contents:
---------

1)  Building the module
2)  Details on building the module (Linux)
3)  Installing the manpages
4)  Compiling the module statically against Apache 1.x

1) Building the library
-----------------------

Please change the PATH settings, APACHEVERSION and the APXS variable 
in the makemod script for your environment.

run as root: ./makemod

2) Details on building the module
---------------------------------

DB2PATH=/home/db2inst1/sqllib
EXTRA_LFLAG="-Wl,-rpath,$DB2PATH/lib"

- If you are using Apache 1.x:

apxs -c -D APACHE1 -ldb2 -lcrypt $EXTRA_LFLAG mod_auth_ibmdb2.c

- If you are using Apache 2.x:
apxs -c -D APACHE2 -ldb2 -lcrypt $EXTRA_LFLAG mod_auth_ibmdb2.c

If the sqlcli1.h header file cannot be found, add the -I option to specify the
directory where sqlcli1.h can be found.
If the db2 library cannot be found, add the -L option to specify the
directory where libdb2.so can be found.
For example:

apxs -c -D APACHE2 -L/home/db2inst1/sqllib/lib -I/home/db2inst1/sqllib/include
 -ldb2 -lcrypt $EXTRA_LFLAG mod_auth_ibmdb2.c

To move the DSO to the modules directory:

- If you are using Apache 1.x:
apxs -i mod_auth_ibmdb2.so

- If you are using Apache 2.x:
apxs -i mod_auth_ibmdb2.la

As the next step the DB2 environment has to be set in the Apache startscript.
You just need to source the db2profile script, which is located in DB2PATH.

Finally, add the following directive to httpd.conf:

LoadModule ibmdb2_auth_module modules/mod_auth_ibmdb2.so

You may also need to add:

AddModule mod_auth_ibmdb2.c

3) Installing the manpages
--------------------------

Change to the ./man directory and run the script
maninstall

4) Compiling the module statically against Apache 1.x
-----------------------------------------------------

Extract the apache source code to a directory (e.g. /ext).

Change into the 'modules' directory:

cd /ext/apache_X.Y.ZZ/src/modules

Extract mod_auth_ibmdb2-x.y.z.tar.gz into the 'modules' directory.

Change into the 'mod_auth_ibmdb2' directory and copy the two files from the 
'static' directory into the current one:

cd mod_auth_ibmdb2
cp static/.indent.pro .
cp static/Makefile.tmpl .

Change into the 'src' directory:

cd ../..

Add the following line to the 'Configuration' file and to the
'Configuration.tmpl' file:

AddModule modules/mod_auth_ibmdb2/mod_auth_ibmdb2.o

Source the db2profile:

. /home/db2inst1/sqllib/db2profile

Run the 'Configure' scipt:

./Configure

Make the server (run 'make' in the 'src' directory).

Add the db2 lib directory to the end of '/etc/ld.so.conf' file and run
'ldconfig'.
